Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.27,0:02:27.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy is diving on us!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.11,0:02:41.28,Sign,,0,0,200,,{\fade(300,0)\c&HFBF2F7&\1a&H00&\b1\blur1\bord0}{ミッドウェイ海戦(前編)}Episode 3 \N{\fs100}Battle of Midway (Part 2){/later/last half}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.60,0:02:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn it! Kaga was hit! {/damaged}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.13,0:02:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Soryu had the same fate!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.96,0:03:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Emergency takeoff! \NEmergency takeoff! {/hurry up to ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.04,0:03:33.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of the 4 Japanese carriers, \N3 burst into flames in a blink of an eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.75,0:03:36.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The only operational carrier left was Hiryu. {/remaining}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.63,0:03:43.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Thus, the Battle of Midway \Nhad become a milestone of the Pacific War. {would assume it's 転機wo画す - a fight that marks the turning point}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.01,0:03:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,As it is pointed out \Nas a stark example {lit: "at the same time, to what extent mistakes in calculations and decisions can the victory into defeat? - some say it was the typical example" - this sounds awful in english so had to deviate a lot here}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.06,0:03:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,of how erroneous decisions and miscalculations
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.23,0:03:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,may turn a certain victory into a disaster.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.24,0:04:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,If during the time of decision making, \Na commander opts to bury his head in the sand,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.87,0:04:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,nothing but defeat can come out of it. {lit: if commanding officer is clinging to/relying on vague hopes in the time of decision, nothing but defeat can be obtained}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.96,0:04:18.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet, the captain of the remaining carrier, Hiryu, was taking a stand. {really dont know what he meant to say by that}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.43,0:04:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Curse it! \NIf only we had 5 minutes more!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.35,0:04:30.06,Default,,0,0,0,,No, not 5 minutes. Our only chance for victory, \Nthat I told you about, slipped away 2 hours ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.06,0:04:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, we've been idling for 2 hours straight! {/wasted ...} \NNow it's our turn! {lit is "this time, I'll do it" but I don't have a slightest clue what he means, that he would assume command next? that his ship is next on the chopping block? that next he is going to act and repel the attack? that he is going to "do" himself with seppuku?}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.59,0:04:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Meanwhile, on Akagi, the flagship.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.36,0:04:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Admiral, I understand your disarray, \Nbut please transfer your flag and take our lead. {/I can understand your feelings well, but please relocate the headquarters and take direction}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.08,0:04:51.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So far, our losses number 3 carriers.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.29,0:04:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,We still have one carrier, 2 battleships, 2 heavy cruisers, \Nand 12 destroyers - a sizable force to be reckoned with! {/we still have a big fleet of ... left}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.91,0:04:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's retaliate with the whole fleet!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.07,0:05:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I leave her to you. {/take care of the rest}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.40,0:05:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Trust us to take care of Akagi. \NOur hopes are with the fleet! {/I will pray for the fleet's success}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.92,0:05:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Hiryu's light signal. {/hiryu's flash/spotlight/searchlight signal}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.40,0:05:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,"Hiryu. Alive and well."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.40,0:05:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,They are urging us to attack. {pressing; urging; demanding; demand}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.47,0:05:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,An order to attack was issued to Hiryu.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.64,0:06:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,As per the patrol aircraft's report, \None enemy carrier is stationed 144 km to the east{ from here}. {nishi is supposed to be the west but I'd assume they either mixed things up or mean something like "we're 144km to the west from the enemy"; irl it was east so IT HAS to be east, okay? maybe north-east at best}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.92,0:06:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Its only escort being vessels and destroyers, \Nour side has a clear advantage.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.21,0:06:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,As of now, I proposed \Na full-scale offensive to the admiral. {nagurikomu is raid; attack; assault}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.53,0:06:13.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, the raid's goal is... {/this attack squadron's aim is...}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.41,0:06:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,To send this carrier to the seabed! {I translated it "Cutting the Gordian Knot!" in the ep1 but here it won't work because it'll be "cutting the enemy carrier in two" which technically works but is not exactly what he means}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.08,0:06:18.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright... An eye for an eye - \Nmake it a reality. {hope it's タリオ当たりでやってくれ - law of talion}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.62,0:06:19.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.33,0:06:57.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Commander, the attackers of Akagi are in my way.{/the guys who did/attacked/crippled akagi}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.21,0:07:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Good. Keep following them, \Ntake care to be stealthy! {/this way so they don't notice you}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.34,0:07:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So, being their cursed shadow? {https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Okuri-inu - I don't know what analogue to use in english}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.81,0:07:17.72,Default,,0,0,0,,There it is! {/I can see it!}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.39,0:07:20.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the carrier! Charge! {/attack}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.38,0:08:33.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, let's do it! {/go}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.43,0:08:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.86,0:08:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Screw you...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.28,0:09:02.41,Default,,0,0,0,,However, that American carrier \Nwas not alone in the area. {/operating alone}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.04,0:09:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,On the bridge of aircraft carrier Enterprise... {艦橋}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.79,0:09:09.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Dispatch the patrol aircraft!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.94,0:09:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.93,0:09:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The report from Yorktown arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.36,0:09:18.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Fires put away. {/immediately}\NIn working order. {/not a big deal/nothing to worry about}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.20,0:09:22.21,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\c&HEAE5DF&\bord0\blur1}Yorktown \N{I don't know what is that sign on the blackboard, a carrier? a radiowave? a shell?}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.26,0:09:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Yorktown is operating normally, it seems. {honestly, this is the first time I'm hearing of this, sounds kinda dumb, the japanese never cracked the american codes and afterwards they went to attack in that area again and even mistook yorktown for another carrier because it hasn't been smoking, falsely reporting 2 carriers sunk; upd: nevermind, it's a data they got from interrogating american pilot, however this is kinda dumb we missed the interrogation sequence. moreover, it's a hella lot of time between bombing yorktown, fixing it, another pilot takes off from it, gets to kidou butai, crashes, gets rescued and interrogated - what a stupid move to skip it all}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.97,0:09:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet, I saw a huge cloud \Nof black smoke rising from it when we left. {黒煙} {/I have confirmed/checked a tremendous amount of smoke is rising from it}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.94,0:09:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been hit 3 times.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.73,0:09:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It's likely out of action. {/let's judge serious damage; drubbing was done}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.48,0:09:36.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The issue is, it was not the only enemy carrier. \NThere are 3 of them. {/it was not alone}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.20,0:09:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly. {/so what?}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.61,0:09:39.53,Default,,0,0,0,,According to the captured pilots, {/According to the evidence from the POW/captured  pilot} {yes, this really happened - american pilot ditched his plane into water, they fished him out and tortured}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.26,0:09:44.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Yorktown, Enterprise, and Hornet carriers \Nare supposed to link up. {union (e.g. of forces); linking up; merging; coming together}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.81,0:09:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Info extorted under torture\Nis unreliable. {/The testimony of the POW cannot be relied upon}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.12,0:09:49.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, it is backed up \Nwith the subsequent patrol reports. {agreement; accord; correspondence; consistency; coincidence}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.63,0:09:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,No room for doubt here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.94,0:09:56.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy is split into two with the two carrier task force much further from the single carrier's. {/much further ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.05,0:10:00.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I see, so there are 3 enemy carriers in the area...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.60,0:10:03.26,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\c&HD6D6D9&\bord0\blur1}Yorktown \NEnterprise          Hornet   \h
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.56,0:10:12.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Tallying with different reports, \NJapan has undeniable firepower. {Lit: Judging comprehensively from the reports, the Japanese army is really strong. - no clue what he means by actually strong, also nippongun is troops/land army and HA had it "navy" somehow so I would assume this is about the rest of japanese still navy laying in ambush (yamato&co)} {gonna make it clear right away: those two are arguing whether or not they should pursue the last japanese carrier, I would assume this is Raymond A. Spruance on-board Enterprise - he is advocating pushing the battle to the end, while the lower-ranking offcier advocated withdrawing to safety, even I'm not sure of it myself as both are doing it in some very indirect way}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.37,0:10:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Our forces should be on par. \NQuite frankly, we may even have the upper hand. {I drop the exact meaning of 1st in favor of a conversation that makes sense so I make it sound as though he says "they aren't that dreadful without those 3 carriers"; HA has second sentence as "It cannot be said that it is excellent in flattery." somehow; I have lit of "Although it is excellent even in flattery" which I have no clue what to make of, would assume "call it a flattery/bragging, I think our fleet condition is excellent"}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.03,0:10:18.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Makes you wonder how they pulled off\Nthat sneak attack before. {/almost makes you wonder how they pulled of a surprise attack} {there's a BIG chance I'm getting this all completely wrong and he really means "What are our forces compared to that? Not very impressive, courtesies aside. Pulling off a surprise attack [on japanese carriers today] was a wonder already/The very fact our surprise attack succeeded is highly bizarre" - but I had already decided it's the lower-ranking officer who is defending the "retreat" point here, so this admiral is supposed to be pro-offense, even if it pains my brain already}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.70,0:10:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Our big asset is the ability \Nto read Japan's radio traffic.{lit: we here have all the intel/info on the japanese side - he refers to US being able to read all the japanese naval radio codes JN25b; alternative in case this whole convo should be the other way around: It was only natural with the amount of intelligence we have on the Japanese. }
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.78,0:10:23.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{I was because }We spotted a golden chance and seized it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.93,0:10:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet, after getting this far, \Nwe're letting the last Japanese carrier go. {lit: still, albeit just one ship, japanese carrier is left/remaining}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.96,0:10:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,,As long as this ship is still out there, the same fate \Nthat befell them today might be ours tomorrow. {lit: what I mean to say is, always, you can't understand if the fate that struck them/that they sustained, becomes our fate or not or "You never know when the fate they've suffered will become our fate." - still no fucking clue what he means, YOU HADFUCKING ALREADY NEARLY LOST YORKTOWN, WHY SAY ALL THE MALARKEY}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.90,0:10:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I propose a withdrawal. \NThe enemy losses are 3 aircraft carriers, ours - one. {/let's pull out}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.07,0:10:39.66,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a huge success as it is. {senka can mean loads of stuff but most likely "military gains; war results; fruit of battle" - this is enough of senka}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.22,0:10:41.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You see an opening - you hit. {lit is "hitting/fighting proper; righteous; just; honest; truthful; lawful" - either he means "hitting would be appropriate here" or "we'll fight them fair and square"}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.61,0:10:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,For this gamble, only Enterprise will engage. {/with this one ship enterprise }
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.60,0:10:45.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I will terminate them myself. {とどめを刺す - to finish off; to ensure (something) is dead; to deliver the coup de grace}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.79,0:10:47.33,Default,,0,0,0,,How about Hornet?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.33,0:10:49.29,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll keep Hornet in the reserve. {honestly this is the first time I'm hearing of this, I was sure they keep operating TF16 as a whole till the end, with hornet and enterprise together, }
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.23,0:10:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,In the event of a Japanese attack coming our way, {/if by any chance the japanese army comes to attack/with a raid}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.96,0:10:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,we'd sacrifice Enterprise, \Nas a price for Hornet's escape. {/use enterprise as a decoy/lure, while hornet runs away}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.98,0:10:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Lets man up and finish this. {originally: "To notch up the big fight?." kessen is decisive battle; deciding match; play-off}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.42,0:10:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Not a fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.09,0:10:59.95,Default,,0,0,0,,A duel.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.57,0:11:02.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a duel!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.45,0:11:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,A carrier versus carrier duel.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.27,0:11:07.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of the 3 enemy aircraft carriers, \None was crippled by Kobayashi's Squadron. {again, serious damage; drubbing; At 8:00 am (11:00), a total of 24 planes , 18 ninety-nine bombers and six Zero fighter planes , commanded by Captain Michio Kobayashi (ship bomber) as the first wave attack squadron, launched [354] [355] . Of the ninety-nine bombs, 12 had 250 kg conventional bombs and six had land-based bombs}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.85,0:11:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll take out at least one more,\Neven if we sink with it! {/with one of the remaining two, we stab each other/to sacrifice oneself in order to harm someone else}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.50,0:11:14.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Left with only one carrier, \Nour fleet will destroy the enemy at night! {he refers to the rest of the fleet - yamato&co}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.79,0:11:17.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The first attack wing is ready to take off. {good bye; I'm off; see you later}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.16,0:11:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Commander. {/squadron chief}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.97,0:11:22.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Your plane only has a half tank \Nworth of gasoline.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.99,0:11:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Feel free to use my plane, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.10,0:11:26.21,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.52,0:11:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,A trifle. Shots scraped my wing away a little. \NWell, I guess this works, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.80,0:11:33.69,Default,,0,0,0,,This way, I can carry more shells. {lit: It's better to have more at once - maybe he is talking about the fuel, but next lines make me think he means bombs}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.69,0:11:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Commander!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.86,0:11:38.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll only need one. \NA torpedo in the middle. {no clue why he specifies it's in the middle, also unsure if he doesn't imply "you'll be fine in your own plane, I don't expect you to come back/you'll only need enough fuel for one way" since that's what eventually happens, but to assume this to be a way to say "this time, we're flying with torpedoes" seems like a more sound proposition}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.41,0:11:39.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.21,0:12:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, that's our clients! Let's go! {maybe this last word is "miro" - look!}
